{"name":"Cahuatelle","size":"large","type":"dragon","tag":"summon","alignment":"","hitDice":"5","armorName":"other","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":3,"otherArmorDesc":"19 (+upcast) (natural armor)","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"20","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"60","hover":false,"swimSpeed":"30","customHP":true,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"60 (+10 per upcast)","speedDesc":"30 ft.","strPoints":"19","dexPoints":"16","conPoints":"15","intPoints":"10","wisPoints":"14","chaPoints":"13","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"9","customCr":"12 (8,400 XP)","customProf":4,"isLegendary":false,"legendariesDescription":"The archmage can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. The archmage regains spent legendary actions at the start of its turn.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the archmage can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the archmage can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The archmage can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isMythic":false,"mythicDescription":"If the archmage's mythic trait is active, it can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using {Some Ability}.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the archmage's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the archmage dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Shared Resistances","desc":"While [MON] is summoned, choose one of its damage resistances.  The summoner has resistance to the chosen damage type until the spell ends."}],"actions":[{"name":"Multiattack","desc":"[MON] makes a number of Constrict attacks equal to half the spell’s level (rounded down), and it uses Blinding Breath."},{"name":"Constrict","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 5 ft., one creature. _Hit:_ [STR 1D6 + 5] (+upcast) bludgeoning damage, and the target is grappled (escape DC 17). Until this grapple ends, the creature is restrained. [MON] is large enough to keep two adjacent creatures grappled, but no more than two. With it has two creatures grappled (but not one) [MON]'s speed is 0."},{"name":"Blinding Breath","desc":"[MON] exudes destructive energy in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 17 constitution saving throw . On a failed save, a creature takes [2d6] damage of a type [MON] has resistance to (your choice) and is blinded for 1 minute. A creature can repeat this save at the end of each of their turns to end the blind. A creature who succeeds takes half as much damage and is not blinded. Once a creature succeeds on this save, they are immune to this affect for 1 hour."}],"bonusActions":[],"reactions":[],"legendaries":[],"mythics":[],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[],"skills":[],"damagetypes":[{"name":"cold","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"},{"name":"lightning","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"},{"name":"necrotic","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"},{"name":"radiant","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"},{"name":"thunder","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"}],"specialdamage":[],"conditions":[{"name":"charmed"},{"name":"frightened"},{"name":"poisoned"}],"languages":[{"name":"Aire","speaks":false},{"name":"Common","speaks":false},{"name":"Dwarvish","speaks":false},{"name":"Halfling","speaks":false},{"name":"Sylvan","speaks":true},{"name":"Undercommon","speaks":false}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"","pluralName":"","doubleColumns":false,"separationPoint":1,"damage":[]}